data.chText: 所有物；财产；财物
data.enText: a thing or things that are owned by sb; a possession or possessions

data.chText: 这座大楼是政府的财产。
小心别损及别人的财物。
data.enText: Be careful not to damage other people's property.

data.chText: 不动产；房地产
房地产的价格大幅上升了。
data.enText: The price of property has risen enormously.

data.chText: 房地产价格
房地产开发商
房屋及院落；庄园；房地产
data.enText: a building or buildings and the surrounding land

data.chText: 这个地区有大量的闲置房地产。
data.enText: There are a lot of empty properties in the area.

data.chText: 性质；特性
data.enText: a quality or characteristic that sth has

data.chText: 比较一下这两种物质的物理特性。
data.enText: Compare the physical properties of the two substances.

data.chText: 药用植物

data.text: building ♦ property ♦ premises ♦ complex ♦ structure ♦ block ♦ edifice

data.chText: 以上各词均指建筑物、房屋、楼房。
data.enText: These are all words for a structure such as a house, office block or factory that has a roof and four walls.

data.chText: 指建筑物、房屋、楼房
data.enText: a structure such as a house, office block or factory that has a roof and four walls

data.chText: 指房屋及院落、庄园、房地产：
data.enText: a building or buildings and the surrounding land; land and buildings

data.chText: 我们有一买主想看看这房产。
data.enText: We have a buyer who would like to view the property.

data.chText: 房地产的价格大幅上升了。
data.enText: The price of property has risen enormously.

data.chText: 谈及买卖房屋或房地产时常用该词。
data.enText: This word is often used when talking about buying/selling houses or other buildings and land.

data.chText: 指企业拥有或使用的建筑及附属场地、营业场所：
data.enText: [pl.] the building or buildings and surrounding land that a business owns or uses

data.chText: 这家公司正在寻找更大的营业场所。
data.enText: The company is looking for larger premises.

data.chText: 指类型相似的建筑群：
data.enText: a group of buildings of a similar type together in one place

data.chText: 休闲活动中心
指结构体、建筑物：
data.enText: a thing that is made of several parts, especially a building

data.chText: 这个码头是木结构建筑。
data.enText: The pier is a wooden structure.

data.chText: 指公寓、办公大楼或学校、医院等作特定用途的大楼：
data.enText: ( BrE ) a tall building that contains flats or offices; a building that forms part of a school, hospital, etc. and is used for a particular purpose

data.chText: 公寓大楼
这所学校的理科大楼
指大厦、宏伟建筑

simple_means.memory_skill: prop 自己的；拥有 + er 表名词 + ty 表状态 → 财产；特性

ex.chText: 她有着孩子般的天真特质。
ex.enText: She has a childlike quality.

ex.chText: 木材的一个特性是可以燃烧。
ex.enText: One quality of wood is that it can burn.

ex.chText: 他在研究该金属的物理和化学特性。
ex.enText: He is studying the physical and chemical qualities of the metal.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，指有形或无形的特性，也可指个性或共性的特征。

ex.chText: 一名优秀的领导者应具备哪些素质？
ex.enText: What attributes should a good leader possess?

ex.chText: 杰克拥有一流运动员应具备的所有特质。
ex.enText: Jake has all the attributes of a first-class athlete.

synonyms.bx: 指某人或某物特有的性质或属性，尤指好的、有用的特质。

ex.chText: 这两组患者具有截然不同的特点。
ex.enText: These two groups of patients have quite different characteristics.

ex.chText: 他最为突出的特点是诚实。
ex.enText: His predominant characteristic is honesty.

ex.chText: 物体的物理特征也应考虑进去。
ex.enText: The physical characteristics of objects should also be taken into account.

ex.chText: 这是他们与众不同的特征之一。
ex.enText: It is one of their distinguishing characteristics.

synonyms.bx: 指有别于其他人或事物的典型的、特殊的、本质的特性或特征，含易于辨认之意，通常用复数。

ex.chText: 这是我们社区大学的一个主要特点。
ex.enText: This is a key feature of our community college.

ex.chText: 眼睛是她五官中最好看的部位。
ex.enText: Her eyes are her best feature.

ex.chText: 韩国食物最显著的特点就是味道辛辣。
ex.enText: The most distinguishing feature of Korean food is the spiciness.

ex.chText: 荷兰重要的景观风貌是什么？
ex.enText: What are the important features of the landscape in Holland?

synonyms.bx: 指引人注目的显著特征或细节，多用于说明人或事物的主要特征，也可用于说明地理特征等。

ex.chText: 没有一部成文宪法是该国的一大特点。
ex.enText: The lack of a written constitution is a peculiarity of the country.

ex.chText: 生有育儿袋是有袋动物的一个特点。
ex.enText: Pouches are a peculiarity of marsupials.

synonyms.bx: 指地方、人、情况等的独特之处。

ex.chText: 我们来比较一下这两种物质的物理特性。
ex.enText: Let's compare the physical properties of the two substances.

ex.chText: 这种容器保温性能很好。
ex.enText: This container has good heat-retaining properties.

synonyms.bx: 多指同类事物所共有的特性，通常用复数。

ex.chText: 遗传的性格特征
ex.enText: genetic traits

ex.chText: 他最讨人喜欢的两大个性特点是慷慨与和蔼可亲。
ex.enText: His two most pleasing traits are generosity and amiability.

ex.chText: 该医学研究以某些性格特征为基础。
ex.enText: The medical research was based on particular personality traits.

synonyms.bx: 多指人的性格或性情特征，尤指先天的性格特征。

tr: any movable articles or objects used on the set of a play or movie
example: before every scene he ran down his checklist of props

tr: a basic or essential attribute shared by all members of a class
example: a study of the physical properties of atomic particles

tr: a construct whereby objects or individuals can be distinguished
example: self-confidence is not an endearing property

tr: any area set aside for a particular purpose
example: the president was concerned about the property across from the White House

tr: any tangible or intangible possession that is owned by someone
example: he is a man of property

value.def: Someone's property is all the things that belong to them or something that belongs to them.

example.ex: Richard could easily destroy her personal property to punish her for walking out on him...
example.tran: 理查德能轻易毁掉她的私人财产来惩罚她对他的背叛。

example.ex: Security forces searched thousands of homes, confiscating weapons and stolen property.
example.tran: 安全部队搜查了数千所住宅，没收了武器和赃物。

value.def: A property is a building and the land belonging to it.

example.ex: Cecil inherited a family property near Stamford...
example.tran: 塞西尔继承了斯坦福德附近的一处家族房产。

example.ex: This vehicle has been parked on private property.
example.tran: 这辆车停在了私人地产上。

value.def: The properties of a substance or object are the ways in which it behaves in particular conditions.

example.ex: A radio signal has both electrical and magnetic properties.
example.tran: 无线电信号具有电、磁双重属性。
